mods:titleInfo.mods:title: The Sphecini Wasps of the Genera Chilosphex BOHART & MENKE, Isodontia PATTON, Palmodes KOHL, Prionyx VANDER LINDEN and Sphex LINNAEUS of the " Biologiezentrum Linz " - Collection in Linz, Austria, (Hymenoptera, Apoidea, Sphecidae)

subSubSection.paragraph:
N o t e: The presence in most females of appressed white setae on the pronotal collar and scutum identifies
S. flavipennis
and separates the species from the similar
S. funerarius
which lacks such pubescense. Unfortunately the appressed setae are poorly developed in some poulations, and in older material they are often worn away. In such cases association with males offer the only reliable means of identification (MENKE & PULAWSKI 2000: 331). Males can be identified by characteristic placoids on flagellomeres V-VII.
